Loop iter24 (2026-05-26): browser-edit-autorecord false-positive fix. autoRecordBrowserEditsFromBody (gm-plugkit wrapper) matched ambiguous .js/.mjs/.cjs/.ts by extension alone while scanning prd-resolve/transition/memorize-fire/mutable-resolve bodies, so Node-only files merely NAMED in a witness string (lib/skill-bootstrap.js, gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js) got recorded as browser edits requiring a witness — would falsely fire deviation.client-edit-no-witness for any Node .js work. Fix: isBrowserRelevantPath(rel,cwd) — unambiguous client exts always; ambiguous js/ts only if path is browser-reachable (browser-dir segment site/public/web/www/client/frontend/ui/assets/static/dist/build/docs OR a sibling .html), and never in node dirs (lib/bin/scripts/gm-plugkit/node_modules/test/.gm). The browser-witness gate (paper §23) must distinguish browser-reachable .js from Node .js; extension alone is insufficient because .js/.mjs/.ts are ambiguous. Validated other 0.1.577 fixes still live: prd-add field-fallback, prd-resolve nested unwrap, widened changelog classifier all PASS, store balanced 57/57.